ON
THE
USE
OF
SIDEJETS
AS
CONTROL
DEVICES
WIND
TUNNEL
EXPERIMENTS
WITH
SIDEJETS
ISSUING
LATERALLY
NEAR
THE
BASE
OF
SLENDER
BODIES
IN
A
SUPERSONIC
STREAM
HAVE
SUGGESTED
THE
EXISTENCE
OF
A
SIZABLE
AND
USABLE
INTERACTION
WITH
THIS
INTERACTION
FORCE
THE
USE
OF
JET
REACTION
CONTROLS
MAY
BE
AS
ATTRACTIVE
FOR
FLIGHT
WITHIN
THE
ATMOSPHERE
AS
IT
OBVIOUSLY
IS
FOR
FLIGHT
OUTSIDE
THE
